%text We have been told which $(x,y)$ to consider in set-builder notation. And what we have been told is % \begin{align} \begin{tabular}{Nl}
\hline \text{Requirement} & Meaning \\ \hline x\geq 0 & Points to the right of the origin \\ \hline y\geq x & Above the line $x=y$ \\ \hline y \leq \sqrt{4-x^2} & Inside the circle $x^2+y^2 = 4$ \\ \hline \end{tabular} \end{align} %text So, the required region is as shown below % \begin{align}
\includegraphics[scale=1.4]{right.svg} \end{align} %text %
